@@eThornwood -- Quarantine Ledger Threat Projection@@N

The @@rQuarantine Ledger@@N classifies Thornwood as a @@rNecrotic
Expansion Hazard, Watch Status@@N. It is not currently a direct
threat to our trade corridors. But the Ledger's Hazard Scribes
think in projections, and this projection is @@runsettling@@N.

Thornwood sits south of the Great Northern Forest's canopy edge.
The @@yLantern Road@@N -- the artery feeding goods into the oasis
corridors and eventually to our docks -- passes through that
forest. If Thornwood expands far enough to contact the Lantern
Road, our supply chain contracts. @@dThe logic is linear and the
Ledger Houses do not ignore linear threats.@@N

The estate's @@rassimilation@@N behavior elevates it above ordinary
hazard. The forest consumed the manor. The manor consumed the
forest. Both were metabolized into a system that treats death as
input and expands accordingly. The @@rWild Hunt@@N -- the estate's
mobile enforcement -- has extended its patrol range toward the
Lantern Road farther than in any prior generation.

If Wild Hunt elements reach trade convoys, the Harbor Wardens
face a classification problem without precedent. Necrotic entities
are not smuggled goods or cursed artifacts -- they are @@ractive
hostile process attached to material@@N. The Quarantine Ledger's
four-tier system was designed for objects, not for biological
intelligences that replicate institutional structure in bark
and bone.

The @@dThornwood Lich@@N retains Lord Harren inside a system he
helped create. This is oath-breaking turned inside out: the
institution consuming the oath-swearer rather than the oath-
swearer betraying the institution. The Shrine of the First
Claw was built to oppose precisely this.

The @@lsubstrate logic@@N -- crystalline formations mediating the
necrotic ecology -- is a Quarantine Ledger concern. Crystal-
mediated phenomena are flagged in our hazard tables regardless
of origin: @@runattested geological power interfacing with
institutional decay@@N.

Standing guidance to the Sand-Sea Carters' Guild: any convoy
reporting necrotic contact along the northern route triggers
Tier Two inspection at the Reach boundary. @@gCargo from the
living is welcome. Cargo from the dead must prove it is not
still serving the dead.@@N

@@dThornwood holds that death is patient and thorough. We intend
to be swifter.@@N
